headline.main: Kentucky’s Bizarre Attack on Health Reform
headline.print_headline: Kentucky’s Bizarre Attack on Health Reform

docs.abstract: Editorial repudiates Kentucky Gov Matt Blevin's decision to discontinue state's health care exchange, noting effort to spite federal government by relying on it to run exchange is bizarrely contradictory; asserts transfer to federal program will be complicated and could leave many uninsured; calls on state to repay $290 million in federal grants it received to build system.

docs.lead_paragraph: Public health officials in Alabama are working to contain a tuberculosis outbreak. They used federal money to pay for tests on more than 1,000 people in one of the poorest counties in America, and found 47 people who are infected and need treatment to keep the disease from spreading.
